ResponseMessage.title: Message

messageType.description: Severity of the problem described by a message.

messageNumber.description: A message number (not including the message level one-letter code) that uniquely identifies the message and can be typically looked up in product documentation.

messageContent.description: Readable message in US English. It should be a proper human-readable sentence.

messageAction.description: Recommendation of the actions to take in response to the message.

messageReason.description: Supplements the 'messageContent' field, supplying more information about why the message is present.

messageKey.description: Unique message key describing the reason for the message in a machine-readable format enabling localization. It should be a dot-delimited string tld.provider.service[.sub-service].detail.

messageParameters.description: Message parameters. Used for formatting of localized messages in conjunction with the 'messageKey' field.

items.description: Message parameter. Can be of any type.

messageInstanceId.description: Unique ID of the message instance. Useful for locating the message in product logs. The same ID should be printed in the product log output.

messageComponent.description: (For support and developers) Identifies the component that generated the message. Can be a fully qualified Java package or class name.

messageSource.description: (For support and developers) Identifies the source service that generated the message.

ResponseMessage.description: User-facing API message and related metadata.
